spec: multiprocessing_extra112
version: ">=3.11"
backend: python_module(multiprocessing)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html — Python multiprocessing module documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html#multiprocessing.pool.Pool — Pool class documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/pool.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends multiprocessing_extra111.zspec.zsdl."
    - "This spec covers: wave 255 theme — multiprocessing.pool.Pool lazy-iterator and async method co_qualname attributes (Python 3.11+) not covered in extra101, extra103, or extra105. The spec imports from multiprocessing.pool; multiprocessing.Pool is a bound method (factory function), not the class itself. NEW in extra112: multiprocessing.pool.Pool.imap.__qualname__=='Pool.imap' (len=9, co_argcount=4); multiprocessing.pool.Pool.imap_unordered.__qualname__=='Pool.imap_unordered' (len=19, co_argcount=4); multiprocessing.pool.Pool.map_async.__qualname__=='Pool.map_async' (len=14, co_argcount=6); multiprocessing.pool.Pool.starmap_async.__qualname__=='Pool.starmap_async' (len=18, co_argcount=6); and their co_qualname values (Python 3.11+): imap co_qualname len=9, imap_unordered co_qualname len=19, map_async co_qualname len=14, starmap_async co_qualname len=18. All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "multiprocessing.pool.Pool.imap.__qualname__ == 'Pool.imap' (len=9: 'Pool.'=5+'imap'=4=9). imap returns an iterator (lazy evaluation, unlike map which returns a list); co_argcount=4 (self, func, iterable, chunksize). multiprocessing.pool.Pool.imap_unordered.__qualname__ == 'Pool.imap_unordered' (len=19: 'Pool.'=5+'imap_unordered'=14=19; longest method qualname in this spec). imap_unordered returns results in the order they complete (not the order of the input iterable); co_argcount=4. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "multiprocessing.pool.Pool.map_async.__qualname__ == 'Pool.map_async' (len=14: 'Pool.'=5+'map_async'=9=14). map_async is the non-blocking variant of map, returning an AsyncResult; co_argcount=6 (self, func, iterable, chunksize, callback, error_callback). multiprocessing.pool.Pool.starmap_async.__qualname__ == 'Pool.starmap_async' (len=18: 'Pool.'=5+'starmap_async'=13=18). starmap_async combines starmap and async behavior; co_argcount=6. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

